      "title": "SIP-31: Reduce the fee for launching farms with Sperax Demeter protocol",
      "content": "Author: Core Team\nReference: Demeter dapp, Demeter protocol docs\nCreated: January, 25th, 2023\nLabels: #Product-Features\n\n## Simple Summary\nThe proposed change will decrease one-time entry fee paid by projects/DAOs launching their farms with Demeter protocol.\n\n## Abstract\nThe proposal sets the fee for a launch of Demeter farms at the level of $50 for farms launched against USDs or SPA and $100 for farms launched against other tokens.\n\n## Motivation\nThe proposed change will decrease the entry barrier for new projects - in comparison to the current fee level - $100 for a farm launched against USDs or SPA and $500 for a farm is launched against other tokens. At the same time, the new fee for launching a farm against USDs or SPA stays less than the fee for launching a farm against non-Sperax tokens.\n\n## Overview\nDemeter is a protocol developed by Sperax, it is an element of the Farming-As-A-Service infrastructure that helps DAOs to launch and manage decentralized exchange liquidity on Uniswap v3 in a low code/no code manner.\n\nSince its inception on November 2022, 12 farms have been launched with Demeter, including:\n\n6 farms launched by Demeter Genesis partners seeding the partners’ tokens against USDs, these farms emit rewards both in partners’ tokens and SPA (2 of those farms were reopen with new parameters).\n3 farms launched by Sperax\n1 farm launched by a non-partnering project that emitted only the project’s rewards, but not SPA.\nThe proposal is to change the one-time launch fees from\n\nthe current levels:\n\n$100 for farms launched against USDs or SPA\n$500 for farms launched against other tokens\nto proposed new fee levels:\n\n$50 for farms launched against USDs or SPA\n$100 for farms launched against other tokens\n\nThis will facilitate access of DAOs to the Demeter services, including those DAOs that potentially might launch farms against tokens other than SPA or USDs. At the same time, the fees for launching farms against USDs or SPA stay more favorable.\n\n## Technical Specification\nSet one-time Demeter farm launch fee at the level of:\n\n$50 for farms launched against USDs or SPA\n$100 for farms launched against other tokens\n\n## Voting\nYes: Set one-time Demeter farm launch fee at the level of $50 for farms launched against USDs or SPA and $100 for farms launched against other tokens.\n\nNo: Keep the current fees unchanged.",
