      "id": "0xbae4b03256b501173cf6dd0e9d277fed5e5a133b7267623350c57a76b74ae09b",
      "title": "SIP-30: Set Sperax DAO Voting Quorum Threshold at 200M veSPA",
      "content": "SIP-30 Set Sperax DAO Voting Quorum Threshold at 200M veSPA\nAuthor: Core Team\nReference: \n[SPA staking analytics ](https://app.sperax.io/stake), [PlutusDAO analytics](https://dune.com/cadmusbenedictus/plutusdao), [Sperax DAO Snapshot](https://snapshot.org/#/speraxdao.eth)\n\nCreated: January, 19th, 2023\nLabels: #Governance-Discussion\n\n## Simple Summary\nThe proposed change will optimize Sperax DAO’s voting quorum threshold. This will serve as a protection against potential governance attacks and will help to increase the attendance of voting veSPA holders.\n\n## Abstract\nThe proposal sets the quorum at the level 200 M veSPA (~⅓ of current total voting power). The current voting quorum of 20M veSPA is relatively small (~3% of total voting power) and is too easy to reach, opening the door to potential governance attacks and disengaging SPA stakers to attend votings.\n\n## Motivation\nThe voting quorum threshold (20M veSPA) is negligible regarding the current total voting power (600M+ veSPA), it is too easy to reach. This might have two negative consequences:\n\npotential governance attacks: the Community will be forced to vote against knowingly spamming/toxic proposals - just to counter such proposals;\ndisengagement of bona fide veSPA holders: as the quorum is easily reachable, they might stay passive and not attend SIP voting if they see their opinion Yes or No is passing without their support.\n\n## Overview\nSperax DAO governance procedure has been implemented last year, the first voting passed on July 2022, and 28 SIP in total were prepared, discussed, and voted. Since the DAO governance inception, the voting threshold stayed at the stable level of 20M - despite SPA staking, and thus total voting power continued to grow, reaching 623M veSPA which includes ~41% of voting power accumulated by Plutus DAO.\n\nAs the voting power grew but the voting quorum threshold didn’t - the current threshold is only 3% of the current total voting power.\n\nSuch a low share is not optimal due to two reasons:\n\nLow threshold means it is relatively easy to collect a quorum and this may be a danger in the case of potentially toxic/spam SIPs acting against the interests of the Sperax Community. The Community will be pulled into voting to counter such proposals. Rising the threshold level will not allow toxic proposals to collect a voting quorum and thus countering voting will not be needed.\n\nLow threshold might disengage bona fide SPA stakers who see the 20M quorum is always reachable, and thus they might be not motivated to vote - if they see their opinion is passing without their support. Rising the threshold level will engage SPA stakers to attend the voting.\n\nThe proposed solution is: to set the DAO voting quorum threshold at the level of 200M veSPA which is ~⅓ of the current total voting power.\n\n## Technical Specification\nSet quorum threshold on Sperax DAO Snapshot at the level of 200M veSPA.\n\n## Voting\nYes: Set the quorum threshold on Sperax DAO Snapshot at the level of 200M veSPA.\n\nNo: Keep the quorum threshold on Sperax DAO Snapshot unchanged.",
